data.title: Amazingly fresh seafood
data.text: Ate lunch at Kathleen's Catch with my mother on October 25th, 2016.  We "ate in", and had 2 each or 4 different kinds of fresh oysters, clam chowder, and a lobster roll.  The food we had was wonderful and the freshness was incredible.  We bought some fresh swordfish steaks to take home and cook and I've not seen an swordfish any fresher.  The prices are Kathleen's Catch are not cheap, but you never feel that you're not getting good value for your money.  I'll be back soon for get some more fish to cook at home.

data.title: NOT A RESTAURANT!!
data.text: Kathleen's Catch is a great place for buying fresh seafood to prepare at home or your hotel kitchenette. But it does *not* belong on TripAdvisor's list of area restaurants. Giving it 5 stars for its seafood selection, modified by 0 stars as a restaurant brings this review to 3 stars overall.

data.title: Wow! Very Impressed!
data.text:
This review is actually about the Milton Location of this fresh seafood shoppe. Wow! what a selection! and being a seafood fanatic i was kinda in heaven. 5 - 6 different kinda of oysters in the shell! yippee! just for clarity, this is a market where you pick it up for cooking etc later. i dont think they actually serve lunch etc there.. could be wrong though.
Sara and staff were very helpful and friendly. i grabbed up as much as i could today and will definitely be back again soon. Super Fresh food. glad i discovered this place. I love seafood! so heal/thy™...

data.title: There Aren't Many Seafood Stores
data.text: Kathleens Catch has been in this location for around 10 years.  I always go here when I want some truly fresh seafood that is above and beyond anything you find at any of the local grocery stores.  The selection of fish to choose from is just really great.  The people working there are very knowledgeable about each fish type and the best ways to cook and season each.  More and more people are trying to lead a more healthy lifestyle and have moved away from so much meat, chicken and pork from their diets.  At KC you can get the same types of seafood/fish that you see at the best restaurants in town, only at a fraction of the cost. Give it a try.

data.title: First time customer
data.text: Lobster rolls and crab cakes were outstanding and clearly all fresh ingredients. We will clearly be using Katheleen's for future dinners.

data.title: Great selection. Great taste. Fish Monger
data.text: If you are looking for a place to help you increase your healthy living this is a great place for fresh fish.  I have never been a fan of having fish cooked at home but Kathleen's helps bring restaurant quality food to your table.

data.title: awesome seafood spot for home cooking
data.text: I have purchased seafood a few times here and it is always fresh. I refuse to pay for certain seafood in restaurants, sea bass for example and we buy it here. it is expensive but worth it. we have bought scallops and fresh fish as well. great spot, great service and great items for sale to add to your fish.

data.title: Alway The Freshest Fish out there
data.text: I have shopped here for years...it is the only play in North Fulton that we can find truly fresh seafood of all types....

data.title: Fresh Selection the BEST in the area bar none, bring your wallet You get what you pay for
data.text: Fresh Selection the BEST in the area bar none, bring your wallet You get what you pay for for once!  Very helpful and attentive staff.  Wish they served prepared dishes all the time

data.title: Great selection, helpful staff
data.text: The selection of fresh seafood is amazing.  Prices are reasonable and staff helpful.  A culinary adventure!

data.title: The Trawler Must Pull Up To The Back Door!
data.text: Fresh varieties of seafood at reasonable prices. Our go to seafood market. You'll find something different every visit.

data.title: Seafood at its Best
data.text: Fresh & Fabulous. We often don't think stand alone markets will offer the freshest seafood. Kathleen's is truly a 'CATCH'. And yes as the other reviews state, the Lobster Roll is amazing. Congrat's Kathleen - much continued success.........

data.title: Lobster Roll Deee-lish!
data.text: We ordered the lobster rolls and it was delicious. Mayonnaise base with a nice warm toasted roll. We had to put the lobster in the roll.  So it seems ideal to take home without having soggy roll.  We ate there. There was only one table located outside for two.  Once the news gets spread about Kathleen's Catch, good luck getting a seat for lunch. Great nonetheless.

data.title: Top Notch
data.text:
At first when I saw that a stand alone fish market was going to open on Whole Foods doorstep, I was skeptical that they could ever hope to compete and survive.

Well not only did Kathleen's survive but they thrived and are opening another store. Why did they survive? Two reasons-- they have the freshest fish and seafood and the best selection carrying unique types of fish that can not be found elsewhere.

If you love to cook and live fish and seafood then you have to go to Kahleens

data.title: Hard to find fresh seafood around here.
data.text: Wow, delicious, fresh fish.  All kinds, every day.  Great to stop by and pick up a fresh cut or maybe a lobster roll.  Right next to a wonderful wine store so you can create a nice meal all at once.

data.title: The place to go for fish
data.text:
Kathleen's is primarily a fish monger as pointed out in other reviews. She does offer a small selection of prepared items such as lobster and shrimp rolls but go here for the fresh fish! She offers the BEST selection and it's always fresh.

Kathleen's is definitely worth a special trip!

data.title: Best seafood in the area
data.text: We've never had an issue with anything we bought here.  Can't say that about Publix, Fresh Market, or even Whole Foods.  Kathleen's seafood is always top-notch.  And a very nice selection as well.  We frequently buy the frozen stuff since it's a little cheaper, and it always defrosts and cooks beautifully. Definite recommendation.

data.title: seafood
data.text: great fresh seafood. large selection of any type seafood from stone crabs to fresh oysters. Good service and they will order anything you wish.

data.title: Best Fishmonger in Atlanta
data.text: This isn't your typical restaurant.  It's primarily a fish market.  Which has some of the best fish in the metro area.  But you can buy pre cooked foods.  Kathleen always has a fish soup or stew available plus she has all kinds of dips just ready for your party.  She will also do party trays for you.  For New Years she did a tray of smoked salmon with cream cheese, capers and red onion as well as cooked shrimp with crab claws with a cocktail sauce and a truffled mayo.  Very very good.  If you're in the north Atlanta suburbs and need some fresh fish or a quick dip, Kathleen's is great.

data.title: Not really a restaurant, but great fish monger
data.text: While Kathleen's does offer some items to go, such as shrimp rolls, lobster rolls, soups and 'heat and serve' dinners, it is not an actual restaurant.  It is a small establishment with awesome fresh fish, shrimp, clams, mussels, scallops and oysters.  You can order live Maine lobster that is delivered the following day at a price far better than eating out at restaurants.  While I'm not a huge fan of the lobster rolls since I don't like celery or may, I can say I will never order lobster out at a restaurant again when I can steam it myself! I have been spoiled by Kathleen's and am diligently spreading the word about this great small business.
